05/03/2009
STRASBOURG, France -- During a debate on Kosovo at the European Parliament in Strasbourg on Wednesday (March 4th), Czech Deputy Prime Minister Alexander Vondra called for the inclusion of Kosovo in the Stabilisation and Association process and the European integration process.
Vondra, whose country holds the rotating EU presidency, conceded "It isn't easy to keep the unity of EU countries on this matter."
In other news Wednesday, Bashkim Smakaj became the first director of the Kosovo Intelligence Agency (KIA), two months later than expected.
Currently a deputy colonel in the Kosovo police, Smakaj will head the KIA for the next five years.
(Koha Ditore, Kohavision, Telegrafi, Express, Zeri, Lajm, Kosova Sot - 05/03/09)
